
 




Report: Creating a Login Page in HTML
1. Overview
This project demonstrates a basic login page created exclusively with HTML. The page is designed to allow users to enter their credentials (username and password) and submit the form. Although this approach uses only HTML, note that in real-world scenarios you would typically combine it with CSS for styling and JavaScript or server-side programming for functionality and security.
2. Design Considerations
â€¢	Simplicity:
The design focuses on simplicity. All elements are laid out in a straightforward manner with clear labels and required fields.
â€¢	User Experience:
Labels are associated with their corresponding input fields using the for attribute, which improves accessibility. The form includes the required attribute to ensure that users cannot submit empty fields.
â€¢	Structure:
The HTML structure is divided into head and body sections. The head includes metadata and the title, while the body contains the content and form elements.
â€¢	Security Note:
Although this example only demonstrates HTML, be aware that HTML alone does not provide any security. Validation, authentication, and encryption should be handled on the server side.
3. HTML-Only Code
Below is the complete HTML code for the login page:
